  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(PPL) Speak Out! - Addressing sexual and reproductive health rights and gender-based violence in Rwanda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Speak Out! is a violence against women and girls (VAWG) and sexual and reproductive health and rights (SRHR) focused project, working with girls, mentors and Women&#x2019;s Rights Organisations (WROs) in Rwanda. It is implemented by ActionAid Rwanda, alongside two local partners &#x2013; Faith Victory Association (FVA) and the Girl Guides Association of Rwanda (AGR) - with the outcome that 5,600 girls and 14 WROs in four districts (Karongi, Nyanza, Gisagara and Nyaruguru) in Rwanda have increased willingness, confidence and ability to report and respond to cases of violence and have increased knowledge of SRHR.</narrative>
  </description>
